Burglaries over the last 12 months are down 8% compared to the annual average over the last three years, according to San Francisco Police Department data through October 30.

The city averaged 116 burglaries a week over the last 12 months. In 2019, that number was 95 a week.

A closer look at San Francisco burglaries neighborhood by neighborhood

The risk is not the same neighborhood to neighborhood. ABC7s data team looked at the San Francisco Police Departments data by neighborhood from 2019 through October 30, 2022.

The map color codes each neighborhood by the burglary rate over the last 12 months. The three darker blues represent neighborhoods with burglary rates that are higher than the citywide rate. You can also click the box in the bottom right corner to see neighborhoods by the number of burglaries.

Click on any neighborhood on the map to see detailed numbers, rates and trends. You can also search for a street name, place, landmark or zip code.
